name: Knighted Guard
desc:
Dons a standard full-body knight armor, wields a sharp sword, and protects the body with a sturdy kite shield.
A solid tank in battle, impeccable in both defense and counterattack.

name: Knighted Pikeman
desc:
Dons a standard mixed knight armor and wields a lance as weapon.
Advances in a formation in battle and leverages the reach of a lance to gain an advantage. Their lance can penetrate thicker armor, and they can take more damage.

name: Axe Knight of the Union
desc:
Dons a knight's armor and wields a giant long-handled axe with both hands.
A vanguard in battle who puts their lives on the line, focusing solely on whacking enemies with a massive axe.

name: King's Army Archer
desc:
Dons a red standard military uniform decorated with striking golden patterns and uses a longbow to attack from a great distance. They are not equipped with armor.
Boasts impressive range and formidable lethality in comparison with other archers. However, carrying a longbow slows them down and the lack of armor renders them vulnerable to attacks.

name: K.A. Fire Conjurer
desc: Dons a hooded uniform exclusive for Irian conjurers and uses crystal balls with inlaid Luxite to launch ranged fire attacks. They are not equipped with armor. Their fire spells can deal damage from a middle or distant range or grant buffs to allies in battle, which renders them well-balanced in attack and support in comparison with fire conjurers from other factions.

name: Outlaw Axeman
desc:
Dresses in a common Irian style, dons a leather armor to protect vital parts, and wields a waraxe in battle.
They are weaker at defense in comparison with berserkers from other factions, but this also grants them a higher agility evident in attack and dodge.

name: Outlaw Pikeman
desc:
Dresses in a common Irian style, dons a leather armor to protect vital parts, and wields a light lance in battle.


They are weaker at defense in comparison with pikemen from other factions, but the lighter lance enables them to swing the weapon swiftly for precise continuous attacks.

name: Outlaw Assassin
desc:
Dresses in a common Irian style, wears no armor, and wields a pair of short daggers in battle.
Their destructive power is limited in comparison with seekers from other factions, but the various traps they carry are enough to deter any enemy.

name: Outlaw Archer
desc:
Dresses in a common Irian style, wears no armor, and wields a short hunting bow in battle.


Despite their modest lethality and range, they boast outstanding mobility which enables them to launch quick, continuous arrow attacks.

name: Outlaw Crossbowman
desc:
Dresses in a common Irian style, wears no armor, and wields a hunting crossbow in battle.
Their crossbow is obviously at a disadvantage in comparison with crossbowmen from other factions, but they have made compensations by upgrading the arrows.

name: Outlaw Guard
desc:
Dresses in a common Irian style, dons a leather armor to protect vital parts, and wields a round leather shield and a one-handed axe in battle.
Their shield, while lacking in defense properties, is better suited for launching counterattacks. Instead of raising the shield in a defense posture, they are more inclined to launch fierce attacks through the coordinated use of the round shield and the hand axe, or simply throw the axe at enemies.

name: Papal Radiant Maidservant
desc:
Dons a gilded headdress with an ethereal veil and a pure white gown adorned with golden threads.
They chant the Radiant Blessing they have perfected over years to channel elements in the Luxite for deadly attacks.

name: Papal Radiant Crossbowman
desc:
Dresses in a common Papal States style with their characteristic hooded trench coat and wields an intricate repeating crossbow in battle. They are not equipped with armor.
Their repeating crossbow can suppress enemies by shooting numerous arrows in a short time. However, their relatively low mobility slows them down to a certain extent.

name: Darklight Ice Priest
desc:
Dons a dark robe embroidered with a Darklight emblem and wields a pair of chanted brass knuckles embedded with tainted Luxite.
They can condense ice crystals into sharp blades, dealing damage over time to a large area in close range. Meanwhile, they are also well-versed in leveraging the power of ice for self-protection.

name: Dawn Maidservant of Darklight
desc:
Dons a black hooded robe to hide the emaciated body and enters the battlefield with an artifact made from tainted Luxite.
Outside the battlefield, they engage in cruel experiments, distorting spirits and corrupting bodies with the darkest parts of Luxite.

name: Darklight Sapper
desc:
Wields a pickaxe, dons a basic helmet, and carries a backpack full of mining explosives.
They throw bombs like crazy, determined to destroy the battered old world. When necessary, they would even sacrifice themselves to bring down the enemies.

name: Paladin
desc: Paladins boasting both strength and fortitude. Their battle performance ranks top in the entire Union of Knight States. With their fierce attacks and high destructive power in battle, they can often single-handedly break down enemy defense, gaining an advantage for allies.

name: Militia Sapper
desc:
Fights with various fire bombs, but wears no armor and carries no shield.
Most of them were bandits before the war. In battle, they are skilled in causing distraction and blocking the enemies' path with flames from an explosion.

name: Recruited Assassin
desc:
Dons dark-colored clothes and a hood to conceal the appearance, protected by leather armor only in a few places.
Their defense and stamina are unparalleled among seekers. By dodging and attacking continuously, they can engage with their targets over a long period instead of relying on a one-shot kill like other seekers.

name: Radiant Knight of the Union
desc:
Dons a lightweight, blue scholar's armor while wielding a battle hammer and a shield.
Tasked with curing the sick in everyday life, they use Radiant Blessing to defeat enemies and support allies in battle.

name: Papal Ice Priest
desc:
Dons a holy chiffon vestment and wields an artifact of purity that dazes opponents.
Possesses better defense skills in comparison with ice conjurers from other factions. In battle, they can create barriers or temporary buildings to protect allies and leverage the power of ice to stop bleeding.

name: Darklight Fire Priest
desc:
An unarmored unit that leverages fierce fire spells to terminate enemies.
As mutants hiding in civil society, they possess a self-awakened power of Luxite resonance, made highly erratic and unstable by Darklight's catalytic influence.

name: Vlderian Dancer
desc:
Dons a hot, exotic dancer's attire and hides a sharp dagger under the thin fabric.
Vlderian dancers, with their intoxicating moves, are in fact agile attackers. The lethality of their attacks is heightened when seamlessly blended with their unpredictable dancing steps.

name: Vlderian Mountain Archer
desc:
Dons a neat outfit and wields a short bow.
Good at climbing. Although the short bow has a limited attack range, their high mobility and remarkable hand-to-hand combat skills still make them terrifying enemies.

name: Wrath Knight
desc:
Dons a paladin's heavy armor and wields a sacred sword.
Despite their lack of mobility, their superb destructive power is enough to make up for any shortcomings.

name: Darklight Crossbowman
desc:
Donned in rags and wields a crossbow made of strings and other scraps.
Compared with crossbowmen from other categories, they have slower shooting speed, shorter range, and less powerful arrows; however, they often use toxic arrowheads or tie explosives to arrows.

name: Darklight Pikeman
desc:
Uses tattered farm tools commonly found in the countryside as weapons. Wears only clothes made of rough cloth or even hangs around in rags.
They excel in agility compared to pikemen from other categories, capable of launching rapid and continuous attacks. But their attacks lack in lethality.

name: Mercenary Girl
desc: A unique guard trained personally by Rawiyah. They boast a balanced fighting style adequate in both attack and defense, with an ability to inspire allies and increase their fighting abilities. A mercenary whose strength and skills are no worse than any elite soldier.

name: Mercenary Boy
desc: A unique archer trained personally by Rawiyah. They are adept at leveraging their mobility to manipulate enemies, waiting for the right moment to deal a deadly blow. A mercenary whose strength and skills are no worse than any elite archer.

name: Vlderian Scout
desc:
Dresses in an agile Vlderian style and wields two daggers in battle. They are not equipped with armor.
Vlderian sentinels, living in the mountains, have acquired the skill of launching raids from elevated positions.

name: Duelling Sword Warrior
desc:
A warrior of the Mercenary Group who wields a heavy claymore and dons a metal armor.
The all-rounded warriors constitute the backbone of the Mercenary Group with their fierce performance in battle.

name: Warrior of the Hanged Men
desc:
A special agent belonging to a secret division of the King's Army. Often wearing a black coat over their red military uniform, the "ominous bats" are the nemesis of all traitors.
Their high mobility and ability to launch combo attacks make up for any lack of defense. Perfect for dealing a decisive assault after an ally has broken down the enemy's defense.

name: Seeker of the Hanged Men
desc:
A special agent belonging to a secret division of the King's Army. Often wearing a black coat over their red military uniform, the "ominous bats" are the nemesis of all traitors.
In battle, they wield a delicate crossbow and a dagger in perfect coordination, pinning enemies and covering allies with the crossbow while leveraging the dagger for a deadly blow. Their high mobility compensates for their lack of defense, and the numerous cooperative techniques with allies make them particularly dangerous and formidable opponents.

name: Prince of Iria
desc:
An agile swordsman. Their performance in direct combat is fairly generic despite the elegant and flowery moves, but they are adept at utilizing tricks and feints to create an advantage in battle, including setting up traps, launching surprise attacks, or stabbing an enemy behind their back.
Utilizes allies to protect themselves or create openings for attack, and leverages Luxite objects to set the stage for surprise assaults.

name: Recruited Guard
desc:
Wields a broadsword as weapon, carries a battered wooden round shield, and dons metal plates only enough to cover the vital parts.
The most mediocre fighting units among mercenaries, balanced in attack, agility, and defense.

name: Recruited Archer
desc:
Wields a longbow as weapon and wears only simple protection.
They can use their longbow to hunt down any prey with great precision, which makes them the nemesis for unarmored units. When facing armored units, they can also distract their target with precise shooting or leverage various abilities to thwart their movement.

name: Recruited Axeman
desc:
Wields a waraxe as weapon and wears no protection except a pair of gauntlets.
These mercenaries are fierce in battle. Their waraxes can launch powerful attacks capable of shattering most shields and armor.

name: Recruited Pikeman
desc:
Wields a lightweight lance as weapon and wears no protection except some cheap helmets, shoulder plates, and gauntlets.
They have an average performance in battle but come at a cheap price.

name: K.A. Pikeman
desc:
Dons a crimson military uniform, wields a standard halberd as weapon, and wears a lightweight metal armor that safeguards vital areas while ensuring agility.
Thanks to rigorous training, these units boast an outstanding group combat ability, but their personal strength remains rather mundane.

name: K.A. Guard
desc:
Dons a crimson military uniform, wields a sword and a wooden kite shield as weapon, and wears a lightweight metal armor that safeguards vital areas while ensuring agility.
Thanks to rigorous training, these units are good at covering allies, but their personal strength remains rather mundane.

name: Calamity Spawn "Drive"
desc:
Tarot Creature - Angry Engine.
These weird fellas with wheels are not really that mad, but their perpetual noise and reckless character give the impression that they are angry all the time.
Still, for an Angry Engine, the rush of racing at top speed and sending obstacles flying is a necessity of life, the same as eating and drinking water.

name: H. M. Commander
desc: Leader of The Hanged Men in the Kingdom of Iria. They possess outstanding leadership abilities, prioritizing a range of command and support skills to guide their subordinates effectively in battle. They also boast decent hand-to-hand combat ability with agile movements and well-trained skills.

name: The Radiant Judge
desc: A judge possessing True Eyes. The True Eyes grant certain predictive abilities in battle, which can help with battlefield command and personal actions. In addition, the maiden's high Luxite adaptation allows her to cast powerful light spells.

name: Guarding Knight
desc: A seasoned old knight with an outstanding ability in assisting and covering allies. In addition, he also boasts a talent in battle command and above-average physical fitness. In battle, he is adept at casting powerful strike-back skills to attack enemies after blocking.

name: Supreme Marshall of Iria
desc: The highest general of the King's Army, a powerful veteran of war. In battle, he always leads the charge against enemies, capable of single-handedly taking down ten enemies with his excellent strength and stamina. His presence boosts the morale of the entire army.

name: General of the King's Army
desc: A young general of the Kingdom of Iria, a high-ranking pikeman who always leads the charge in battles. Adept at disrupting enemy formation with charges and jumps, creating opportunities for the main forces.

name: Nightmare
desc: A war machine of Darklight. He was once an ordinary human before being transformed into a monster by the high priest of Darklight through Luxite Blessing. His ultrahuman strength and stamina are a nightmare for all enemies.

name: Intelligence Officer of the Hanged Men
desc: Battle not ready yet, vacant for now

name: Militia Guard
desc:
An armed civilian in rags without any protection. From a professional perspective, the tools they wield can hardly be called weapons.
Wields a knife and shield modified from everyday tools. Unimpressive in all aspects. Beyond serving as cannon fodder, they struggle to find a meaningful role in battle.

name: Militia Axeman
desc:
An armed civilian in rags without any protection. From a professional perspective, the tools they wield can hardly be called weapons.
Their "long-handled waraxes" are in fact iron shovels. Unimpressive in all aspects. Beyond serving as cannon fodder, they struggle to find a meaningful role in battle.

name: Militia Crossbowman
desc:
An armed civilian in rags without any protection. From a professional perspective, the tools they wield can hardly be called weapons.
Wields a crude crossbow made from wood and cane. Unimpressive in all aspects. Beyond serving as cannon fodder, they struggle to find a meaningful role in battle.

name: Darklight Assassin
desc:
A seeker that dons the dark purple cape of Darklight and wields a short knife.
All recruits of Darklight's armed forces used to be underclass civilians without professional training, so their battle performance is rather unimpressive.

name: Darklight Guard
desc:
Dons plain garments sewn from rags and wields a knife and shield modified from everyday tools.
All recruits of Darklight's armed forces used to be underclass civilians without professional training, so their battle performance is rather unimpressive.

name: Darklight Axeman
desc:
Dons crude cloth garments and wields an iron shovel as a long-handled waraxe.
All recruits of Darklight's armed forces used to be underclass civilians without professional training, so their battle performance is rather unimpressive.

name: K.A. Scout
desc:
A scout of the King's Army who dons a standard Irian military uniform and wields two short knives.
Boasts high mobility, adept at ranged surprise attacks and backstabbing, and possesses a team support ability rare for seekers.

name: Calamity Spawn

Tarot Creature - Minion Tarot.
The most common Tarot Creature.

name: Mimic avatar of Tarot Creature - The Judge
editor_name: 塔罗生物·审判者拟态化身
desc:
Tarot Creature - General Mimic.
A powerful Tarot Creature taking the form of a famous general among judges of the Papal States of Rodinia.
Under normal circumstances, Tarot Creatures do not have the power of mimicking real-life characters. But for some unknown reason, people who once had a strong emotion or obsession may have a Tarot Creature with a similar appearance in this world.
However, there is no natural or supernatural connection between the pair. Defeating the mimic in the Tarot World will have no bearing on its original version in the real world.

Under normal circumstances, Tarot Creatures do not have the power of mimicking real-life characters. But for some unknown reason, people who once had a strong emotion or obsession may have a Tarot Creature with a similar appearance in this world.
